PHP/Python PDF Watermarking v0.06 - Th92
    A simple application to watermark a PDF file.

Requirements:
    PHP 5.x
    Python 3.x
        Modules: os, sys, io, PyPDF2, reportlab

Usage:
    1. Place PDF files in the root directory
    2.a Run the python (./assets/lib/lib.pdf.watermark.py) script from commandline giving the following parameters:
        -i path to the input file (Required, default: "./dummy.pdf")
        -o path to the output file (Required, default: "./dummy.merged.pdf")
        -t text to write as watermark (Required, default: "Copia per TEST")
    2.b Use the WatermarkPDF.php as a REST API passing the parameter:
        i = base64 encoded path to the pdf (default: "./dummy.pdf")
            - This parameter is optional
        t = base64 encoded text to write as watermark (default: "Copia per TEST")
            - This parameter is optional
            - In case no user is defined in PHP from Apache the default is TEST
    2.c Spin a local webserver by using "php -S 127.0.0.1:8000" starting in the root folder then navigate to the index.php page